---
import BlogPostLayout from '../../../layouts/BlogPostLayout.astro';

const title = "Halo Wars 2 - Operation Spearkbreaker Walkthrough";
const description = "Complete walkthrough for Operation Spearbreaker DLC in Halo Wars 2. Covers strategies, unit usage, and mission objectives for both missions on Heroic difficulty.";
const category = "Walkthroughs";
const publishedDate = "Published on February 8, 2026";
const dateIso = "2026-02-08";
const tags = ["Halo Wars 2"];
const ogImage = "https://res.cloudinary.com/damu0vqmp/image/upload/Spearbreaker_Walkthrough_2024_rxopod";
---

<BlogPostLayout
  title={title}
  description={description}
  category={category}
  publishedDate={publishedDate}
  dateIso={dateIso}
  ogImage={ogImage}
  youtubeId="WxWnwAIB2Ak"
  tags={tags}
>
  <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
    Operation Spearbreaker is a DLC campaign for Halo Wars 2, consisting of two missions. This walkthrough covers strategies, unit usage, and mission objectives for completing the campaign on Heroic difficulty.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-cyan-400 mb-4">Mission 1</h2>

  <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-cyan-300 mb-3">Objectives</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-6 ml-4 text-gray-300">
    <li>Capture and control the control towers</li>
    <li>Defend your base from enemy attacks</li>
    <li>Control power nodes for resources</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-cyan-300 mb-3">Key Units and Leader Powers</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-6 ml-4 text-gray-300">
    <li><strong>Leader Powers Available:</strong> Holographic Decoy, Scatterbomb, and Bunker Drops</li>
    <li><strong>ODST Squad:</strong> Unique unit with a drone that shoots a laser and has an EMP ability similar to Johnson's</li>
    <li><strong>Hellbringer Squad:</strong> Available early in the mission</li>
    <li><strong>Wolverines:</strong> Essential for dealing with air units</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-cyan-300 mb-3">Strategy Tips</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-6 ml-4 text-gray-300">
    <li>Use bunkers to protect your units from enemy fire</li>
    <li>Leader powers are individual - each player has their own set</li>
    <li>Power nodes provide continuous power income and should be prioritized</li>
    <li>Restoration drones are important for healing units</li>
    <li>The mission map is similar to the multiplayer map Mirage</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-cyan-300 mb-3">Base Management</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-6 ml-4 text-gray-300">
    <li>Build supply pads and generators early</li>
    <li>Upgrade supply pads when you have enough power</li>
    <li>Control power nodes to generate additional power income</li>
    <li>Mini bases can be captured but require careful defense</li>
    <li>Bases can be destroyed easily, so maintain defensive structures</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-cyan-300 mb-3">Difficulty Notes</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-8 ml-4 text-gray-300">
    <li>The game does not pause during cutscenes, so units can take damage</li>
    <li>Heroic difficulty is challenging, with Legendary being extremely difficult</li>
    <li>Random beams can appear and kill units, which increases frustration rather than difficulty</li>
    <li>The campaign punishes players for looking away from their units</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-cyan-400 mb-4">Mission 2</h2>

  <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-cyan-300 mb-3">Objectives</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-6 ml-4 text-gray-300">
    <li>The Forerunner ship launches in 15 minutes - time management is critical</li>
    <li>Destroy enemy structures and units</li>
    <li>Control key positions on the map</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-cyan-300 mb-3">Key Units</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-6 ml-4 text-gray-300">
    <li><strong>Grizzly Tanks:</strong> Powerful units that should be protected at all costs</li>
    <li><strong>Colossus:</strong> Can be called down as a leader power - referred to as "Gundams" due to appearance</li>
    <li><strong>Nightingale:</strong> Can be rescued and provides healing support</li>
    <li><strong>Combat Tech Marines:</strong> Effective against air units</li>
    <li><strong>Hornets:</strong> Useful air units that can be upgraded</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-cyan-300 mb-3">Strategy Tips</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-6 ml-4 text-gray-300">
    <li>Time is limited - prioritize objectives efficiently</li>
    <li>Grizzly Battalion leader power can be saved up for and dropped strategically</li>
    <li>Build turrets to defend bases from air attacks</li>
    <li>Use scatter bombs effectively against enemy units</li>
    <li>Wolverines are essential for dealing with enemy air units</li>
    <li>Combat Tech Marines work well alongside vehicles</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-cyan-300 mb-3">Base and Economy</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-6 ml-4 text-gray-300">
    <li>Build multiple bases for redundancy as they can be destroyed</li>
    <li>Focus on upgrading to Tech 3 for advanced units</li>
    <li>Vehicle depots are important for producing tanks</li>
    <li>Armories provide unit upgrades and population increases</li>
    <li>Supply crates can be found throughout the map for additional resources</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-cyan-300 mb-3">Enemy Encounters</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-8 ml-4 text-gray-300">
    <li>Retriever Sentinels are major threats that require coordination to defeat</li>
    <li>Enemy bases are well-defended and require significant firepower</li>
    <li>Air units can be problematic if not countered properly</li>
    <li>The mission features multiple enemy strongholds that must be cleared</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-cyan-400 mb-4">General Tips</h2>

  <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-cyan-300 mb-3">Unit Management</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-6 ml-4 text-gray-300">
    <li>Marines can self-heal when using restoration drones</li>
    <li>Units gain veterancy from combat, but not while moving</li>
    <li>Micro-management is important for dodging beams and projectiles</li>
    <li>Split units to avoid area-of-effect damage</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-cyan-300 mb-3">Leader Powers</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-6 ml-4 text-gray-300">
    <li>Holographic Decoy can be used to distract enemies</li>
    <li>Scatterbomb is effective against grouped units</li>
    <li>Bunker Drops provide instant defensive structures</li>
    <li>Grizzly Battalion drops three Grizzly tanks with Pelican support</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-cyan-300 mb-3">Campaign Difficulty</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-6 ml-4 text-gray-300">
    <li>The campaign difficulty on Heroic and Legendary can be unforgiving</li>
    <li>Random beams appearing to kill units is a controversial difficulty mechanic</li>
    <li>Halo Wars 1 had a more balanced campaign difficulty</li>
    <li>Consider playing on Normal if Heroic becomes too frustrating</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-cyan-300 mb-3">Co-op Notes</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-6 ml-4 text-gray-300">
    <li>Players share population cap</li>
    <li>Leader powers are individual to each player</li>
    <li>Units can be transferred between players</li>
    <li>Communication is key for coordinating attacks and defense</li>
  </ul>
</BlogPostLayout>
